# KML → GeoJSON → CSV Converter - Harita Hive Data Tool
# MIT License
#
# Drag-drop format transformer with metadata cleaner
# Supports batch conversion with attribute mapping
#
# Features:
# - Drag-and-drop interface
# - Batch conversion processing
# - Attribute mapping and transformation
# - Metadata cleaning and standardization
# - Coordinate system conversion
# - Data validation and error reporting
#
# Supported Formats:
# Input: KML, KMZ, GeoJSON, CSV, Shapefile, GPX
# Output: GeoJSON, CSV, KML, Shapefile, GeoPackage
#
# Conversion Features:
# - Preserve original styling (where possible)
# - Handle nested folder structures
# - Extract embedded images and attachments
# - Coordinate precision control
# - Attribute name standardization
#
# Data Cleaning:
# - Remove empty attributes
# - Standardize date formats
# - Clean special characters
# - Validate coordinate ranges
# - Detect and fix encoding issues
#
# Attribute Mapping:
# - Custom field name mapping
# - Data type conversion
# - Value transformation rules
# - Conditional field creation
# - Calculated field support
#
# Usage:
# kml-converter --input tour.kml --output data.geojson --clean-metadata
# kml-converter --batch-convert kmz_files/ --output-format csv --mapping config.json